{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"3hrr6","text":"The First Law of Language Silliness","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6eq4c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9o7lq","text":"Every single language and developer tool has that one dumb thing. That one 'feature' the developers added that no one else does and they'll swear up and down is correct. This is despite all evidence to the contrary. ","type":"blockquote","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"chv1p","text":"You could run into it anywhere, the day you go to Production or 2 steps after Hello World. The story is always the same though, \"We are right, you are wrong. It doesn't matter if every other language does it this way we are special and unique snowflakes. Do it our way.\"","type":"blockquote","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6neoc","text":"This principle is universal and unbreakable. It is the closest I've ever been to a proof for God.\" - James Grant","type":"blockquote","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"544it","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1fmvu","text":"Examples","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ffb34","text":"Python: No case statements. Do magic with dictionary statements. Case statements are a CS 101 pattern in every language... except python.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4ckf","text":"IntelliJ IDEs: KeyboardInterrupt does not work in the integrated terminal. VS Code is free and can handle this, the $200 professional IDE can't.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"144la","text":"NodeJS: No sleep or time.sleep statements. Wrap everything in setInterval. Sleep statements are a CS 101 pattern in every language... except NodeJS. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"685nn","text":"Go: No dependency versioning in go get. Use go dep instead. Auditing your supply chain for vulnerabilities and malicious libraries is critical. Go is the only language I've seen move their 'one thing' to something else.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"drj6g","text":"Bash: Internal Field Separator. Boilerplate, set IFS='<enter key>'. The IFS is a neat feature but I've never once used the single space default.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ev6sq","text":"PHP: Janky lexicon. Get nostalgic for \"Lady Marmalade\" and \"U Remind Me\". No choice on this one, you have to learn how we named things 18 years ago.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"knrt","text":"Java: Java. You either work with the Apache foundation or are stuck with it for legacy reasons. Run.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2d5a","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"60d0c","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}